          "reviewTitle": "Great for controlling oil and comparable to higher-end brands",
          "reviewText": "I\u2019ve been really happy with this foundation. I have combination/oily skin, and this does a great job of keeping my skin from getting greasy throughout the day, which is usually my biggest issue. The finish stays nicely matte without looking dry or heavy, and it holds up well for everyday wear without breaking down after a few hours. Coverage is solid\u2014medium to full\u2014and it evens everything out without looking cakey. The shade 370 Toast was also a great match for my skin tone, which can be hard to find without going too light or too orange. I also like that it has SPF 15 built in, so it adds a little extra sun protection for daily use, which is a nice bonus. Honestly, this performs just as well as some of the more expensive foundations I\u2019ve tried, including MAC. For the price, it\u2019s a great value. Overall, if you\u2019re dealing with oily skin and want something reliable that doesn\u2019t cost a ton, this is definitely worth it.",
